00:13:12.400 --> 00:13:14.680
because Nagisa killed me.

00:13:16.610 --> 00:13:20.980
Because the honest bloodlust of this killer toward me

00:13:20.980 --> 00:13:23.910
filled the void in my heart with warmth.

00:13:26.200 --> 00:13:29.980
So with what face—with what words—do I give him this?

00:13:32.070 --> 00:13:32.980
Nagisa?

00:13:34.880 --> 00:13:39.670
Thank you for staying by my side this whole year.

00:13:40.750 --> 00:13:41.530
Here!

00:13:42.200 --> 00:13:43.200
For me?
Yep!

00:13:44.080 --> 00:13:47.880
B-But, I mean, I'm the one who should be thanking you.
Okay, mission accomplished! Well done!

00:13:47.430 --> 00:13:48.780
See you tomorrow!

00:13:48.780 --> 00:13:50.780
Hope you get into that school!

00:13:50.780 --> 00:13:52.250
Uh, yeah...

00:13:53.190 --> 00:13:56.800
Right now, Nagisa is looking straight ahead.

00:13:56.800 --> 00:13:59.910
Being next to him, I shouldn't distract him.

00:14:00.640 --> 00:14:03.320
But I do want to do something to thank him,

00:14:03.940 --> 00:14:06.400
so I'll use my sharpest blade—my acting—

00:14:06.900 --> 00:14:09.300
to cheer him on with my very best smile.

00:14:13.570 --> 00:14:17.580
To kill yourself for someone else at the moment of truth...

00:14:18.040 --> 00:14:21.130
That part of her is a lot like Yukimura-sensei.

00:14:21.130 --> 00:14:24.300
Ah, how noble.

00:14:25.210 --> 00:14:28.260
No way can I poach from someone so admirable.

00:14:28.800 --> 00:14:29.640
Say what?

00:14:29.640 --> 00:14:31.280
Nothing.

00:14:31.280 --> 00:14:32.950
And more importantly...

00:14:33.870 --> 00:14:37.100
What, exactly, has Korosensei so enthralled?

00:14:37.100 --> 00:14:43.070
Oh, I got Kayano-chan to leave a certain photo along with some chocolates and a note in an obvious location.

00:14:43.070 --> 00:14:47.360
 To Korosensei From my sister

00:14:43.070 --> 00:14:44.590
 To Korosensei From my sister A photo?

00:14:43.520 --> 00:14:47.360
 To Korosensei From my sister

00:14:44.590 --> 00:14:48.730
If I'd known it'd work so well, I'd have used it in an assassination.

00:14:52.950 --> 00:14:55.640
A top-class dinner on Valentine's Day...

00:14:55.640 --> 00:14:57.620
I should have expected such thoughtfulness from you.

00:14:58.840 --> 00:15:02.220
I've heard men have to give back threefold on White Day next month.

00:15:02.220 --> 00:15:07.920
I'll accept no less than triple the length and girth,

00:15:07.920 --> 00:15:10.880
Ka-ra-su-ma.

00:15:10.880 --> 00:15:11.640
I'm out.
Huh?

00:15:12.050 --> 00:15:14.430
Hey, wait! Wait! Stay and eat!

00:15:14.430 --> 00:15:16.300
Regular-sized is just fine!

00:15:16.300 --> 00:15:19.360
I'll even make do with fun-sized!

00:15:19.360 --> 00:15:22.940
Such low-class company for such a high-class place.

00:15:24.550 --> 00:15:25.860
Here. It's from Hinano.

00:15:26.320 --> 00:15:28.430
She asked me to give it to you,

00:15:28.430 --> 00:15:31.280
since you're barely at school anymore.

00:15:31.280 --> 00:15:34.250
Once I see an opening, he's mine!

00:15:34.250 --> 00:15:35.470
Or so she said.

00:15:36.270 --> 00:15:39.080
She's reading too much into us. We're not even dating.

00:15:40.560 --> 00:15:42.170
And the others?

00:15:42.170 --> 00:15:45.420
There were more chocolates than I'd thought, both obligatory and heartfelt.

00:15:46.200 --> 00:15:51.440
Maybe some of them thought it might turn out to be their last Valentine's Day on Earth.

00:15:51.440 --> 00:15:54.280
And? What about you?

00:15:54.970 --> 00:15:56.930
How's the assassination going?

00:15:58.460 --> 00:16:02.570
"The probability's down to one percent! Hooray!"

00:16:02.570 --> 00:16:04.760
Like it'll end there.

00:16:05.520 --> 00:16:10.250
So that's why she booked us a private room at a trustworthy establishment.

00:16:11.460 --> 00:16:15.080
Yes. I was planning to talk to you about that.

00:16:15.990 --> 00:16:19.990
My main job now is simply to provide guidance to the E Class,

00:16:19.990 --> 00:16:23.620
so they won't bring me into the loop until the moment of truth.

00:16:24.310 --> 00:16:25.080
But...

00:16:25.710 --> 00:16:31.620
There's no doubt that the powers that be are moving forward with a tremendous assassination project.

00:16:34.550 --> 00:16:37.120
To see it again like this... it's just amazing.

00:16:37.120 --> 00:16:39.530
Can this really kill him?

00:16:39.530 --> 00:16:45.080
With this weapon, it's not a matter of whether it can.

00:16:45.080 --> 00:16:49.850
What's crucial is just how smoothly and how smartly it'll do the job.

00:16:52.010 --> 00:16:55.700
A brutally gorgeous figure for such a virtuous mind...

00:16:58.680 --> 00:17:04.990
Not very commendable, seeing one of our teachers laid low by a single swimsuit snapshot.

00:17:04.990 --> 00:17:07.630
Mr. Principal, sir! Where'd you come from?!

00:17:07.630 --> 00:17:10.090
There are problems with your work attitude.

00:17:10.090 --> 00:17:11.880
I'll be cutting your salary this month.

00:17:12.680 --> 00:17:14.090
Have mercy!

00:17:14.680 --> 00:17:16.540
Yukimura-sensei, was it?

00:17:17.120 --> 00:17:19.300
A shame we had to lose such talent.

00:17:19.880 --> 00:17:24.150
She had an inexhaustible vitality and such passion for teaching.

00:17:24.150 --> 00:17:27.950
Given a few more years, she would have been an outstanding instructor.

00:17:27.950 --> 00:17:29.110
Indeed.

00:17:29.110 --> 00:17:33.780
By the way, I hear there's a chance your life may be saved.

00:17:34.340 --> 00:17:40.460
If so, would you care to follow in her footsteps and teach here next year as well?

00:17:40.460 --> 00:17:45.910
Your artificial-looking expression and physique are well-suited to teaching at this isolated campus.

00:17:47.240 --> 00:17:51.160
I'm flattered. Knowing your policy of judging teachers purely on aptitude

00:17:51.160 --> 00:17:54.250
without being led astray by sentiment or one's past,

00:17:54.250 --> 00:17:58.760
a request for me to stay is the best report card I could hope for.

00:17:58.760 --> 00:18:04.180
Roll Book Roll Book Roll Book Roll Book Roll Book
But I've decided that this will be my last year at the blackboard.

00:18:04.180 --> 00:18:04.220
Roll Book

00:18:04.520 --> 00:18:05.680
And after that?

00:18:05.680 --> 00:18:10.190
Who knows? Perhaps I'll sail around the world.

00:18:11.360 --> 00:18:16.750
Having you for a rival made this school truly enjoyable for me.

00:18:16.750 --> 00:18:19.210
I really must thank you again.

00:18:20.360 --> 00:18:21.370
That's too bad.

00:18:21.940 --> 00:18:24.440
You turned me down before I could bribe you.

00:18:25.540 --> 00:18:29.820
Now that I think about it... I rule this school from the top,

00:18:29.820 --> 00:18:33.480
while you and Yukimura-sensei supported your students from the bottom.

00:18:34.070 --> 00:18:37.180
That might just be my educational ideal.

00:18:38.420 --> 00:18:40.650
By the way, how's your son?

00:18:40.650 --> 00:18:44.430
Ah, he's putting together a ruling hierarchy for high school.

00:18:44.430 --> 00:18:47.900
At this rate, he'll have the whole place under his thumb within the year.

00:18:49.350 --> 00:18:51.340
Truly a remarkable young man.

00:18:51.340 --> 00:18:53.790
Oh, he's not quite there yet.

00:18:53.790 --> 00:18:55.860
There's no end to the ways in which he's still lacking.

00:18:57.810 --> 00:18:59.770
You know, Karasuma,

00:18:59.770 --> 00:19:03.610
I think it might not be so bad if the world were destroyed.

00:19:03.610 --> 00:19:05.330
For the kids, anyway.

00:19:06.450 --> 00:19:11.270
If they can't kill him, they'll be left with these nagging feelings of frustration and loss.

00:19:11.790 --> 00:19:15.470
Worse, if their teacher were killed in some huge assassination

00:19:15.470 --> 00:19:17.780
that was out of their league and beyond their control...

00:19:18.300 --> 00:19:22.080
Or if they were made to witness their mentor's cruel and painful death

00:19:22.080 --> 00:19:25.540
at the hands of some conflicted assassin...

00:19:28.020 --> 00:19:29.640
I'm frankly frightened.

00:19:29.640 --> 00:19:32.220
The frustration, the powerlessness, the trauma...

00:19:32.220 --> 00:19:35.270
No matter how it turned out, such an experience would warp those kids' futures.

00:19:36.980 --> 00:19:42.410
I don't want to see those blameless brats turn into adults with twisted hearts.

00:19:43.890 --> 00:19:44.870
Irina.

00:19:47.120 --> 00:19:49.880
Once this job is over, quit.

00:19:50.460 --> 00:19:51.960
You're not cut out to be an assassin.

00:19:53.080 --> 00:19:54.630
What did you say?

00:19:54.960 --> 00:19:57.010
Your emotions run too deep.

00:19:57.010 --> 00:19:59.560
They've grown fatally so this past year.

00:20:00.090 --> 00:20:03.080
If you feel such emotion for your students,

00:20:03.080 --> 00:20:05.470
it'll only make any future jobs that much harder.

00:20:10.020 --> 00:20:13.280
A stiff like you can blow it off easily enough,

00:20:13.280 --> 00:20:15.650
this life I've desperately built for myself...

00:20:16.560 --> 00:20:18.230
I've killed a lot, you know.

00:20:18.230 --> 00:20:20.760
There's no going back to a place in the sun—

00:20:20.760 --> 00:20:24.160
not with these ten sin-stained years behind me.

00:20:25.090 --> 00:20:28.380
Every experience is a tool that can clear your way to the future.

00:20:29.330 --> 00:20:34.290
It was none other than those students who taught me that.

00:20:34.720 --> 00:20:36.280
There's no need to worry about them.

00:20:36.280 --> 00:20:38.640
No matter what difficulty they may face,

00:20:38.640 --> 00:20:41.160
the experience they've gained through assassination

00:20:41.160 --> 00:20:43.510
will nourish them as they find their own answers.

00:20:44.500 --> 00:20:47.240
Irina, come work for us.

00:20:48.290 --> 00:20:51.770
I'm sure your experience will be put to good use in peacetime too.

00:20:52.840 --> 00:20:55.300
The Intelligence Department won't ask about your past.

00:20:55.300 --> 00:20:57.720
There, you can save more people than you've killed

00:20:58.570 --> 00:21:02.090
and pray for your victims at the shrine every morning.

00:21:02.650 --> 00:21:03.770
That's enough.

00:21:05.360 --> 00:21:07.160
Shrine?

00:21:07.160 --> 00:21:09.850
I'm technically a Christian, you know.

00:21:09.850 --> 00:21:12.200
And I have no family in Japan.

00:21:13.560 --> 00:21:17.910
Don't you get it? There aren't any churches near my house.

00:21:22.420 --> 00:21:24.720
Whaaat?!

00:21:25.020 --> 00:21:27.980
Wait, Karasuma! What are you saying?!

00:21:25.600 --> 00:21:37.500
komorebi ga yasashiku sashikomu ookina mado no naka
As the dappled sunlight shone gently through the window

00:21:27.980 --> 00:21:29.570
Just what I said.

00:21:29.570 --> 00:21:32.970
B-But a man and a woman living under one roof is so...

00:21:32.970 --> 00:21:33.730
immoral!

00:21:33.730 --> 00:21:35.100
Live alone, then.

00:21:35.100 --> 00:21:37.370
No! I'll do it! I'm coming!

00:21:37.370 --> 00:21:40.020
Wait up! Karasuma!

00:21:37.500 --> 00:21:47.760
kimi to deatta ano hi wo tooku ni kanjita

00:21:37.500 --> 00:21:59.920
The day I met you felt so far away 

00:21:49.410 --> 00:21:59.000
sukoshi zutsu narabeta omoi ga boku wo atatameru
The memories I've arranged little by little keep me warm

00:22:00.390 --> 00:22:12.020
chiisana heya tsunagu kokoro sotto oshiete kureta
A small room, hearts connecting: you taught me gently

00:22:12.020 --> 00:22:24.810
kono kisetsu ga mukae ni kitara kimi no sugata mou sagasu koto mo
Once this season comes for me, I won't be able

00:22:24.810 --> 00:22:30.050
dekinaku nacchaun da ne dekinaku nacchaun da ne
To seek you out anymore, will I?

00:22:30.050 --> 00:22:35.690
zutto wasurezu ni iru yo zutto wasurezu ni iru yo
But I'll hold your memory in my heart

00:22:35.690 --> 00:22:41.670
mata kimi ni aeru hi made mata kimi ni aeru hi made
Until the day I can see you again